metas.description:
Teqplay is a context broker providing information and tools to empower the shipping industry to make smarter and better informed decisions in both planning and execution. Our aim is to improve asset utilization, spot opportunities in time and reduce waste in operational costs on fuel (CO2 reduction) and labor.

The behavior of ships and terminals doesn’t adapt continuously and in real time to the dynamics in the changing world. That’s why insight information, both real-time and predicted, is needed. This enables adaptive decision making for shipowners, charterers, terminals and port authorities.  We allow for smarter up-front planning. Our technology monitors the execution and enables the industry to pro-actively adapt and coordinate.
 
Via 24/7 monitoring of vessels, port operations and the external circumstances, we can share the insight. Simply because we know the actual status and history, and we can predict the future with machine learning and AI. Moreover, we provide a single point of truth based on open data sources for each port, allowing for an easy bootstrap. This single point of truth can be shared among the different port call stakeholders in order to optimize decision making. The single point of truth will be enhanced if more and more stakeholders will share their data, allowing us to create even more sophisticated solutions.

We deliver solutions for port call optimization and maritime supply chain optimization, covering both sea and inland domain, including planning of quays, vessels, bunkering and ship to ship transfer. Our solutions are developed in close collaboration with our customers. They provide insight where potential gains or saving can be achieved and empower our clients to convert this insight into real profits and cost savings.

1. Although there are many photo editing and sharing apps, there is still lacking for a community for parents & babies where they can not only share photos but also discuss their daily parenting issues or their pregnancy problems. 
2. Existing social networking sites are too noisy to discuss sensitive baby and pregnancy issues, while also lacking proper photo editing tool for sharing precious maternal memory. 
3. Editing photos of babies need special tool like stickers, different text fonts etc. that is not present in current photo sharing apps. 

Our goal is to fill the gap by providing parents a space (“Giggly”), where they can ask questions for the duration of getting pregnant to raising their child and get help from other parents who might have experienced the same problems before. We are trying to help making parenting easier for new parents and expectant parents, by building an engaged community where they can share, discuss their pregnancy/baby development, issues and get advice,comments from people who have also gone through the same situations.
